Length = Total length of canoe
Lp = Length of paddlers’ “box” (distance btwn first and last paddler)
Ld = Horizontal (x) Distance from bow to deepest point of canoe 
Lf = Distance from bow to first paddler
W = Nominal beam (max width) of canoe (the actual beam is in general smaller than this value due to the smoothing paramters
t1 = Waterline smoothing parameter (bow side)
t2 = Waterline smoothing parameter (stern side)
d = Deepest canoe depth
b = Bow rocker (how far up the bow is relative to deepest point of canoe)
s = Stern rocker (how far up the stern is relative to deepest point of canoe)
f = Flare angle of the flange
shape_param/n= Cross-section shape parameter varying between 0 (rounded bottom) to 1 (flat bottom)
density = density
cp  = volumeofwaterDisplaced/(Waterline*hullcrosssectionarea). measures how close ur canoe looks like to a prism (higher cp means it looks more like a rectangular prisim)
bowpower = exponent used for the curve of the bow (used as 4)
sternpower =  exponent used for the curve of the stern (used as 4)
numstations: Number of pieces we're splitting the canoe into for the  (101)
increment = how long each section is 
keel = longitudnal spine of the canoe
totcm = total canoe mass (people + canoe)

vertCenterMass = Vertical center of mass, different for males/females 
.df = dataframe created 